SOP: Blast Furnace Auxiliary Cooling Leak

1. Notify furnace control room, shift in-charge, and safety officer.
2. Confirm shell temperature, tuyere cooling water flow, pressure, and hydrogen alarm status.
3. Reduce blast or isolate affected branch according to hot repair permit.
4. Lock out local energy sources and protect personnel from hot metal splash.
5. Replace failed tuyere or cooling component, pressure test, and verify no leak before ramp-up.
